org.osmdroid.views.overlay

Class Polygon

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.osmdroid.views.overlay.Overlay
      • org.osmdroid.views.overlay.OverlayWithIW
        • org.osmdroid.views.overlay.Polygon
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    OverlayConstants

    public class Polygon
extends OverlayWithIW
    A polygon on the earth's surface that can have a popup-InfoWindow (a bubble). Mimics the Polygon class from Google Maps Android API v2 as much as possible. Main differences:
    - Doesn't support: Z-Index, Geodesic mode
    - Supports InfoWindow.
    See Also:
    Google Maps Polygon

      • setInfoWindow

        public void setInfoWindow(InfoWindow infoWindow)
        Set the InfoWindow to be used. Default is a MarkerInfoWindow, with the layout named "bonuspack_bubble". You can use this method either to use your own layout, or to use your own sub-class of InfoWindow. Note that this InfoWindow will receive the Marker object as an input, so it MUST be able to handle Marker attributes. If you don't want any InfoWindow to open, you can set it to null.
        Overrides:
        setInfoWindow in class OverlayWithIW
        Parameters:
        infoWindow - the InfoWindow to be opened when tapping the overlay. This InfoWindow MUST be able to handle an OverlayWithIW (as BasicInfoWindow does). Set it to null to remove an existing InfoWindow.

      • draw

        public void draw(Canvas canvas,
                 MapView mapView,
                 boolean shadow)
        Description copied from class: Overlay
        Draw the overlay over the map. This will be called on all active overlays with shadow=true, to lay down the shadow layer, and then again on all overlays with shadow=false. Callers should check isEnabled() before calling draw(). By default, draws nothing. changed for 5.6 to be public see https://github.com/osmdroid/osmdroid/issues/466
        Specified by:
        draw in class Overlay
